body_html:
Are you trying to fix the test failures in http://ci.tensorflow.org/job/tensorflow-master-win-cmake-py/ ?
I think you should upgrade the version of the protobuf pip package on Jenkins slaves. Currently, the kokoro slaves are using a different version as the jenkins slaves. If you revert this change, tests will fail on kokoro.

That would also fix the test failures in the Bazel build.
See #16656

body:
Are you trying to fix the test failures in http://ci.tensorflow.org/job/tensorflow-master-win-cmake-py/ ?
I think you should upgrade the version of the protobuf pip package on Jenkins slaves. Currently, the kokoro slaves are using a different version as the jenkins slaves. If you revert this change, tests will fail on kokoro.

That would also fix the test failures in the Bazel build.
See https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/issues/16656
